ivardefs.name: channel
ivardefs.desc: Details where to send notifications when resources are received that meet the criteria.

ivardefs.name: contact_
ivardefs.desc: Contact details for a human to contact about the subscription. The primary use of this for system administrator troubleshooting.

ivardefs.name: end
ivardefs.desc: The time for the server to turn the subscription off.

ivardefs.name: error_
ivardefs.desc: A record of the last error that occurred when the server processed a notification.

ivardefs.name: eventCount
ivardefs.desc: A record of  the number of events for which the server has attempted delivery on this subscription (i.e., the number of events that occurred while the subscription is in an "active" or "error" state -- not "requested" or "off").   Server Initializes to 0

ivardefs.name: filterBy_
ivardefs.desc: The filter properties to be applied to narrow the topic stream.  When multiple filters are applied, evaluates to true if all the conditions are met; otherwise it returns false.   (i.e., logical AND).

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: A formal identifier that is used to identify this code system when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance.

ivardefs.name: name
ivardefs.desc: A natural language name identifying the subscription.

ivardefs.name: reason
ivardefs.desc: A description of why this subscription is defined.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of the subscription, which marks the server state for managing the subscription.

ivardefs.name: topic
ivardefs.desc: The reference to the topic to be notified about.

properties.desc: The subscription resource describes a particular client's request to be notified about a Topic.
